# .env.production
# SEKAR Mobile — PRODUCTION template (copy to .env.production, then encrypt)
#
# Production API is the on-prem (pemkot) server. After filling real values:
#   npm run env:encrypt          # encrypts .env.staging + .env.production in place
# then commit the ENCRYPTED .env.production (secrets become `encrypted:…`).
# Build:  npm run build:android:production   (decrypts to .env.runtime at build time)
# Needs DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY_PRODUCTION in the environment (or local .env.keys).
# See specs/deployment/encrypted-secrets.md.

# ========================================
# API — on-prem production
# ========================================
